{
  "texts": [
    "The correlation function is therefore localised to the set of points on M g,n where the covering map Γ of (4.6) exists.",
    "To be concise, we will denote correlation functions (before the integral over moduli space) byD({x i, w i, z i }) = n-2+2g α=1 W (u α) n i=1 V w i m i 1,m i 2 (x i; z i),which has support only on the points in moduli space where a covering map exists.",
    "Moreover, we must have thatMg,n D({x i, w i, z i }) = Γ C Γ, (4.7) JHEP04(2024)048where C Γ are ordinary functions of the corresponding fixed points in moduli space and {x i, w i, m i 1, m i 2 }, since the integrand can only be non-zero at the discrete points in moduli space where a covering map Γ exists.",
    "The C Γ do not depend on the insertion points {u α }, since these correspond to the (σ 2 -spectrally flowed) vacuum [7].Under the assumption that the C Γ in (4.7) are non-zero, the above properties are sufficient to show that this distribution precisely satisfies the sampling property of the delta function, by integrating against a test function that is a continuous function of the moduli.",
    "Such localization in M g,n is common in twistor string theory [49,59]."
  ]
}